          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFTPDwDDTnU0wCutUQIQzs8ZPUCQ50dI572qKqeqCAy_nDEg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "As one of the professors of this university hospital explained, you should not go there in spring - autumn period, because the treatment is primarily provided by the newly hired interns. Indeed, I was admitted in summer with severe abdominal pain and spent 5 days in this hospital. I was seen by a few dozens of interns, misdiagnosed (liver cyst) and discharged with even more severe pain. I saw the interns' academic advisor only twice for 2-3 min total - he had no interest in talking to me or changing the orders of the interns. Next week after the discharge, I went to a gastroenterologist. He diagnosed a plain duodenal ulcer. The pain was reduced in 1 day. The testing and treatment took ~3 weeks.",
